docs.abstract: Something like this was tried 18 years ago, when AOL bought Time Warner. But Marc Benioff, long a prominent figure in his hometown, does things his own way.
docs.snippet: Something like this was tried 18 years ago, when AOL bought Time Warner. But Marc Benioff, long a prominent figure in his hometown, does things his own way.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Marc Benioff is like the Salesforce Tower: He looms over this city.

headline.main: A San Francisco Tech Mogul Buys a Fabled Slice of New York Media

byline.original: By David Streitfeld, Don Clark and Natasha Singer

docs.abstract: The storied weekly spent less than a year as part of the Iowa-based Meredith Corporation. Its new owners, Mr. Benioff and his wife, are buying it for $190 million.
docs.snippet: The storied weekly spent less than a year as part of the Iowa-based Meredith Corporation. Its new owners, Mr. Benioff and his wife, are buying it for $190 million.
docs.lead_paragraph: Time, the pre-eminent weekly newsmagazine of the 20th century, will have new owners: Marc Benioff, the billionaire co-founder of the software company Salesforce, and his wife, Lynne.

headline.main: Time Magazine Is Bought by Marc Benioff, Salesforce Billionaire
headline.print_headline: Time Magazine Will Be Sold To Co-Founder Of Salesforce

byline.original: By Amy Chozick and David Gelles

docs.abstract: While having a massage late Sunday, the West Coast-based tech billionaire discussed via text message why he was entering the East Coast-based media industry by acquiring Time Inc.’s flagship publication.
docs.snippet: While having a massage late Sunday, the West Coast-based tech billionaire discussed via text message why he was entering the East Coast-based media industry by acquiring Time Inc.’s flagship publication.
docs.lead_paragraph: Marc Benioff, the chief executive of the software company Salesforce, and his wife, Lynne, said on Sunday that they had agreed to buy Time magazine from Meredith Corporation for $190 million in cash.

headline.main: Marc Benioff Explains Why He Is Buying Time Magazine

docs.abstract: The decision by the Salesforce chief executive Marc Benioff to buy Time magazine raises the question of the duty that executives have to the companies that made them rich.
docs.snippet: The decision by the Salesforce chief executive Marc Benioff to buy Time magazine raises the question of the duty that executives have to the companies that made them rich.
docs.lead_paragraph: If Time magazine runs another cover in a series of illustrations showing President Trump’s Oval Office taking on water, employees and shareholders of Salesforce might want to brace for a tweetstorm from the White House — or even calls for regulation of the software company.

headline.main: When an Owner’s New Company Puts the Old One in Trump’s Cross Hairs

docs.abstract: Marc Benioff has bought Time, becoming the latest technology mogul to invest in a media property.
docs.snippet: Marc Benioff has bought Time, becoming the latest technology mogul to invest in a media property.
docs.lead_paragraph: “This is a start-up,” Marc Benioff told me loudly over FaceTime, leaning in and out of the frame on a bumpy ride to the airport. “They have been opportunity constrained,” he said, “but we are here to unshackle them.”

headline.main: Can the People Who Almost Brought Down the News Business Save It?
